
--[ Settings in Vermin Mud ] --

   You can change your settings with the set command.
   The command format is:

   set <variable> <value>

--[ Available variables ] --

   .-----------------------------------------------------------.
   | Variable   | Values   | Description                       |
   |------------+----------+-----------------------------------|
   | verbose    | on / off | Whether to show the long          |
   |                       | description of rooms when moving. |
   |------------+----------+-----------------------------------|
   | idleprompt | on / off | Whether to display the prompt     |
   |            |          | when idle (ie. every tick).       |
   |------------+----------+-----------------------------------|
   | showrounds | on / off | Whether to display notification   |
   |            |          | when a new battle round begins.   |
   |------------+----------+-----------------------------------|
   | showexp    | on / off | Whether to display exp gains.     |
   |------------+----------+-----------------------------------|
   | prompt     | text     | The prompt to display.            |
   |            |          | See also: prompt                  |
   |------------+----------+-----------------------------------|
   | surname    | text     | Set your surname.                 |
   |            |          | NOTE: You can do this only once.  |
   |------------+----------+-----------------------------------|
   | title      | number   | Select a title from titles        |
   |            |          | available to you.                 |
   '-----------------------------------------------------------'
